.TH DELPHI-COLORBLIND 1  "delphitools-cli 0.1.0" "delphitools manual"
.SH NAME
colorblind \- Simulate colour blindness on an image or a colour
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcolorblind\fR [\fB\-\-cb\-type\fR] [\fB\-\-colour\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIINPUT\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Simulate colour blindness on an image or a colour
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-cb\-type\fR \fI<CB_TYPE>\fR [default: deuteranopia]
Type: normal, protanopia, deuteranopia, tritanopia, protanomaly, deuteranomaly, tritanomaly, achromatopsia, achromatomaly
.TP
\fB\-\-colour\fR
Treat the input as a colour string rather than an image path
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
[\fIINPUT\fR]
Input image file, or a colour string when used with \-\-colour
